// http://stackoverflow.com/questions/16914098/how-to-select-id-with-max-date-group-by-category-in-postgresql
//How to select id with max date group by category in PostgreSQL?

#input

id,  category,  date
1,   a,         2013-01-01
2,   b,         2013-01-03
3,   c,         2013-01-02
4,   a,         2013-01-02
5,   b,         2013-01-02
6,   c,         2013-01-03
7,   a,         2013-01-03
8,   b,         2013-01-01
9,   c,         2013-01-01

#output

id,  category,  date
2,   b,         2013-01-03
6,   c,         2013-01-03
7,   a,         2013-01-03

# constraint
{
	"constants": [ ],
	"aggregation_functions": ["max"]
}

#solution

```sql
SELECT
    T0.id,
    T1.category,
    T0.date 
FROM
    input1 AS T0 
JOIN
    (
        SELECT
            category,
            max(date) AS max_date 
        FROM
            input1 
        GROUP BY
            category
    ) AS T1 
        ON T1.category = T0.category 
        AND T1.max_date = T0.date 
ORDER BY
    T0.id ASC
```
